getEnumerationValues

public CommandParameterEnumValue[] getEnumerationValues()
Returns the enumeration values. If this parameter is not of type CommandParameterType.ENUMERATION, returns null. For a dynamic enumeration parameter, the enumeration values must be queried from the management service.

Returns:
the enumeration values, or null if this parameter is not of an enumeration type.

isLegalParameterValue

public boolean isLegalParameterValue(Object value)

Checks whether an object is a legal parameter value for the parameter defined by this definition. What constitutes a legal parameter value depends on the type of the parameter.

  • For a parameter of type CommandParameterType.STRING, the object must be of type String.
  • For a parameter of type CommandParameterType.INTEGER, the object must be of type Integer and the integer value must be within the range specified by the minimum and maximum values of this parameter definition.
  • For a parameter of type CommandParameterType.ENUMERATION, the object must be of type String and must be the value of one of the enumeration values defined by this parameter definition.
  • For a parameter of type CommandParameterType.DYNAMIC_ENUMERATION, the object must be of type String.

Parameters:
value - the parameter value.
Returns:
true if the specified object is a legal parameter value according to this definition, false otherwise.
